# File Naming Conventions

## Python Files

- Use lowercase with underscores: `tokenizer.py`, `attention.py`, `gpt.py`
- Keep names descriptive: `model_config.py`, `training_config.py`
- Follow existing patterns in codebase
- Organize by domain: `tokenization/`, `model/`, `training/`, `evaluation/`

## Documentation Files

- Use descriptive names with numbering: `01_study_plan.md`, `01_repository-structure.md`
- Number sequentially when order matters
- Use hyphens for multi-word names in URLs

## Configuration Files

- `pyproject.toml`: Project dependencies and configuration (uv)
- `.python-version`: Python version pin
- `.env`: Environment variables (not committed)

## Notebook Files

- Use descriptive names with chapter prefix: `01_ch02.ipynb`, `02_ch03.ipynb`
- Include chapter number for organization
- Keep notebook names clear about content

## Test Files

- Use `test_` prefix: `test_tokenizer.py`, `test_attention.py`
- Mirror source structure: `tests/tokenization/test_tokenizer.py`
- Keep test names descriptive
